
== Rosetta code isn't a blogging site ==

Hi, welcome (belatedly) to Rosettacode. I don't want to discourage you too much as you are at least mostly sticking with programming related content, but this isn't a blogging site and may not be the best place for such a complicated vanity page with dozens of off-site links. There isn't anything necessarily ''wrong'' with off-site links, but it makes it tedious to police for spam links, and fighting spam is a constant battle.

In your over 125 contributions to the site so far, over 100 have been edits to your user page, around 15 to various template and language pages and none actually contributing to a task. You are certainly enthusiastic, but I think you are missing the point. Please don't take this as an effort to get you to leave. You seem knowledgeable about some languages that aren't well represented on the site. I'm just trying to shift your focus a bit. --[[User:Thundergnat|Thundergnat]] ([[User talk:Thundergnat|talk]]) 19:46, 31 January 2017 (UTC)

